pageContext.claim: “I demand transparency from Democrats that went to Ukraine and attempted to force the new President to do things that they wanted under the form of political threat.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump is twisting things. Sens. Chris Murphy (D-Conn.) and Ron Johnson (R-Wis.) met with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky, and Murphy said he "made it clear to him [Zelensky] that Ukraine should not become involved in the 2020 election and that his government should communicate with the State Department, not the president's campaign." He did not threaten to withhold Democratic support for Ukraine in Congress.
